result.execSummary:
The defendant Patrick Allen Ziebell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intentionally Mistreat Animals, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 951.02.
  • Intentionally Mistreat Animals, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 951.02.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:44 AM Defendant Patrick Allen Ziebell in court, in custody.  Attorney Ellen Denise Craker in court for Patrick Allen Ziebell.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. State calls witness. Witness sworn and testifies. Tina Marie Anrig, Community Service Officer, Police Department. State direct exam. March 24, 2022, City of Superior.  Objection as to date, complaint indicates January date. Objection overruled. State clarifies these alleged charges first take place in January. Search warrant executed March 24, 2022, seized dogs and brought to Humane Society. Witness identifies defendant. Court notes identification of defendant. 
Attorney Craker cross exams. Objection, relevance. Overruled. 
State redirects.
No further witnesses.  State presents Exhibit 1 to the Court, bail bond sheet from 21CF428. No objection. Exhibit 1 received. State rests.
State makes argument for bind over. Attorney makes argument in opposition. Court finds probable cause and binds the Defendant over for Arraignment. 
Court reminds the Defendant of their bail conditions.  Defendant provided notice.
Craker addresses bond conditions. Not able to post that amount. Defendant wishes to go to Farmin Center. Has been making all court appearances in his other matter. Asks for signature bond. 
State opposed to modification.  Believes amount set is a reasonable amount. Treatment not related to this matter. Cites prior conviction and prior FTA's. 
Court notes in 21CF428, $500 cash was ordered for a single felony. Court believes cash appropriate. Request denied
Arraignment scheduled for May 9, 2022 at 09:30 am.
